definition.value: An aldohexose used as a source of energy and metabolic intermediate.
An alkaloid isolated from Discosia rubi that is chaetoglobosin A with a methyl substituent on C-10.
A composition-only glycan consisting of four hexosyl groups, five acetaminohexosyl groups and one sulfate group (identities and connectivity unknown). Composition: Hex4 HexNAc5 S1.

A composition-only glycan consisting of two hexosyl groups, two acetaminohexosyl groups and two N-acetyl-neuraminic acid groups (identities and connectivity unknown). Composition:  Hex2 HexNAc2 NeuAc2.
A muconic semialdehyde having a hydroxy substituent at the 2-position.

A composition-only glycan consisting of five hexosyl groups, seven acetaminohexosyl groups, one 6-deoxy-hexosyl group and two N-acetyl-neuraminic acid groups (identities and connectivity unknown). Composition: Hex5 HexNAc7 dHex1 NeuAc2.
A composition-only glycan consisting of three hexosyl groups, three acetaminohexosyl groups and four 6-deoxyhexosyl groups (identities and connectivity unknown). Composition: Hex3 HexNAc3 dHex4.

Any organobromine compound that is used as a flame retardant. These chemicals are widely incorporated as additives in consumer products such as electronics, vehicles, polyurethane foams etc, to make them less flammable.

A composition-only glycan consisting of seven hexosyl groups, six acetaminohexosyl groups and one N-acetyl-neuraminic acid group (identities and connectivity unknown). Composition: Hex7 HexNAc6 NeuAc1.
A composition-only glycan consisting of seven hexosyl groups, six acetaminohexosyl groups and two 6-deoxyhexosyl groups (identities and connectivity unknown). Composition: Hex7 HexNAc6 dHex2.

A member of the class of indolizines that is 3,5,6,7-tetrahydroindolizine which carries a 2-aminoacyl-4-amino-4-oxobutanoic acid, oxo, amino groups at positions 3S, 5 and 6S, respectively. It is a ribosomally encoded and post-translationally modified peptide natural product found in several species of the Pantoea genus and derived from a Glu-Glu-Asn precursor peptide.
An inorganic lithium salt having hexafluorophosphate(1-) as the counterion. It is an electrolyte used in lithium-ion batteries.
An inorganic sodium salt having hexafluorophosphate(1-) as the counterion. It is an electrolyte used in sodium-ion batteries.
A pyrimidine ribonucleoside 5'-diphosphate having cytosine as the nucleobase.

A hydroxyether which contains both an ether and alcohol functional groups. It is one of the most versatile classes of organic solvents which are commonly used in paints, cleaners, adhesives, pharmaceuticals and cosmetics.
A steroid sulfate oxoanion obtained by deprotonation of the carboxylic acid and sulfate functions of cholic acid 7-sulfate; major species at pH 7.3.
A steroid sulfate oxoanion obtained by deprotonation of the carboxylic acid and sulfate functions of glycocholic acid 7-sulfate; major species at pH 7.3.
A steroid sulfate oxoanion obtained by deprotonation of the carboxylic acid and sulfate functions of taurocholic acid 7-sulfate; major species at pH 7.3.
A steroid sulfate oxoanion obtained by deprotonation of the carboxylic acid and sulfate functions of chenodeoxycholic acid 7-sulfate; major species at pH 7.3.
A steroid sulfate oxoanion obtained by deprotonation of the carboxylic acid and sulfate functions of taurochenodeoxycholic acid 7-sulfate; major species at pH 7.3.
